detail.title: Validation Settlement
detail.description:
Hello everyone. I am Alfred from team XPLA.

I propose the phase 2 of Validation Settlement, which plays an important role in the security and governance of XPLA. 

In the Whitepaper, the initial goal of the Validation Settlement was provided for stabilization of validators participating in XPLA chain node operations. 

This approach prevents malicious and monopolistic decision-making that could harm the ecosystem, while fostering an environment where validators actively participating in governance can contribute to ecosystem development.

Now, a year after the launch of XPLA Mainnet, more than 50 prominent validators are participating in our ecosystem and it is running steadily without any block issues.

We believe that we have achieved the initial goal of stabilizing the validation.

Therefore, I propose to switch the Validation Settlement to Phase 2, focusing on expanding and revitalizing the ecosystem through active ecosystem participation of stakers and validators. 

Starting with Phase 2 of Validation Settlement, we have proposed a governance proposal - Proposal #52, which was to change the parameter for fee pool rate to increase the reward of validators by Validation Settlement.

The Validation Settlement with the new phase will attract more participants to the XPLA ecosystem. 

Validation Settlement Phase 2

TL;DR

- Validation Settlement 2.0 Program: In the Phase 2, Validation Settlement volume is returned to the XPLA ecosystem as TX fee over a long period of time. 

- Automatic Redelegation : Periodically redelegate Validation Settlement volume only for the validators that meet the conditions.

- This proposal will be executed within one month of the proposal being passed.

Please see the details below. 

- Validation Settlement 2.0 program 

1) Validation Settlement 2.0 program generates 1 tx per 1 block. 

2) The tx generated by Validation settlement 2.0 program spends fee from the Validation Settlement volume, which runs out over a long period of time.

3) The tx fee generated by Validation settlement 2.0 program consists of [ TX Fee + Contribution Fee ].

 3-1) Contribution Fee is calculated as follows and thus varies from block to block.

2 x [{(the amount of remaining XPLA in Validation Settlement) + (the amount of remaining XPLA in Fee store wallet)} / (the amount of initial Validation Settlement volume, 60 million XPLA)] x [{15 - (Average number of TXs per block in the last 3 months)} / 15] 

4) The tx generated by Validation settlement 2.0 program contains program-related contents for each block, so the Validation Settlement 2.0 program is managed transparently.

5) TX occurs in a separate new wallet under Validation Settlement, and Fees consumed are also deducted from this wallet. 

6) Part of Validation Settlement volume moves to separate Fee store wallet every quarter for TX Fee.

7) XPLA that is moved to Fee store wallet is not delegated to the validators. 

- Automatic Redelegation

1) Redelegation is scheduled to be done by the snapshot of specific blocks each quarter.

2) The subjects of Validation Settlement program are the active validators who has self-bonded more than 10,000 XPLA

2-1) The Self-Bonded condition pertains to the accountability associated with the delegation of the Validation Settlement.

2-2) Conditions may be the subject to change, and the governance proposal must be precedent for the amendment. 

3) Redelegation of Validation Settlement is distributed based on the percentage of pure Voting Power of each validator, excluding the Validation Settlement volume.

4) For the measurement of ‘pure Voting Power’, API addresses that contain the Voting Power information will be used, and users the average value over 3 months to prevent the abuse of snapshot method

5) To prevent the monopoly of the Validation Settlement volume, it is limited to 3 million XPLA for Validation Settlement delegation at most.

- Expectation of the effect on XPLA Chain

We expect that the Validation Settlement 2.0 Program will solidify the staking of XPLA. This would also support the governance community of the XPLA chain more actively and securely. In addition, it is expected to transparently induce the participation of the validator through Automatic Redelegation.

* The information above may be the subjects of change through the governance over time after Phase 2 transition.

detail.title: Parameter change for fee pool rate to increase the reward of validators by Validation Settlements
detail.description:
It has been a year after the Proposal #2 has been up by Delight team, and I believe that we have enough Community Pool by the current distribution.
I suggest the reward distribution to increase the validator rewards by modifying the fee pool rate of Validation Settlement as below.

detail.title: [re]Increase minimum deposit to protect XPLA network from SPAM
detail.description:
First and foremost, we would like to express our gratitude for the Proposal #13 suggestion provided by xpla.staking-explorer.com.

Due to the recent parameter modifications, we are proposing a modification that follows Proposal #13.

We recommend altering the minimum deposit required to submit a governance proposal for the XPLA network.
Upon approval of this proposal, the minimum amount required will be revised from 10 XPLA to 300 XPLA.
This adjustment aims to mitigate the risk of spam proposals and governance abuse.

Sincerely,

Proposer: Alfred Yun, XPLA Teams

detail.title: XPLA proposes to use 70,000 XPLA tokens from the Community Pool to provide liquidity on Osmosis DEX.
detail.description:
What is Osmosis?
Osmosis is a cross-chain DeFi hub within the IBC ecosystem, facilitating approximately 200 million USD in monthly trading volume and boasting a Total Value Locked (TVL) of about 120M USD.

As the liquidity center and primary trading venue of Cosmos – the open, emergent ecosystem of sovereign Layer 1s connected with the Inter-Blockchain Communication protocol (IBC) – it is the access point for the wide world of appchains, the gateway to the interchain.

Osmosis is continuing to expand its moat as the only full-service, cross-chain exchange and DeFi hub, one that rivals the smooth user experience of a CEX without compromising on the benefits of decentralized finance – self-custody, trust-minimized transactions, direct on-chain access, and privacy.

XPLA intends to provide liquidity to Osmosis to create an environment with improved accessibility that allows users from the IBC ecosystem to participate in XPLA's ecosystem as if it were their own. By connecting to the IBC ecosystem, XPLA's ecosystem can expand to various other ecosystems. This presents an opportunity for XPLA to reach a broader audience and attract new users/consumers to its games and entertainment content.

Proposal:
XPLA proposes to use 70,000 XPLA tokens from the Community Pool to provide liquidity on Osmosis DEX.

By voting "Yes," you agree to allocate 70,000 XPLA tokens from the Community Pool as liquidity on Osmosis DEX.
By voting "No," you disagree with allocating 70,000 XPLA tokens from the Community Pool as liquidity on Osmosis DEX."

messages.title: XPLA proposes to use 70,000 XPLA tokens from the Community Pool to provide liquidity on Osmosis DEX.
messages.description:
What is Osmosis?
Osmosis is a cross-chain DeFi hub within the IBC ecosystem, facilitating approximately 200 million USD in monthly trading volume and boasting a Total Value Locked (TVL) of about 120M USD.

As the liquidity center and primary trading venue of Cosmos – the open, emergent ecosystem of sovereign Layer 1s connected with the Inter-Blockchain Communication protocol (IBC) – it is the access point for the wide world of appchains, the gateway to the interchain.

Osmosis is continuing to expand its moat as the only full-service, cross-chain exchange and DeFi hub, one that rivals the smooth user experience of a CEX without compromising on the benefits of decentralized finance – self-custody, trust-minimized transactions, direct on-chain access, and privacy.

XPLA intends to provide liquidity to Osmosis to create an environment with improved accessibility that allows users from the IBC ecosystem to participate in XPLA's ecosystem as if it were their own. By connecting to the IBC ecosystem, XPLA's ecosystem can expand to various other ecosystems. This presents an opportunity for XPLA to reach a broader audience and attract new users/consumers to its games and entertainment content.

Proposal:
XPLA proposes to use 70,000 XPLA tokens from the Community Pool to provide liquidity on Osmosis DEX.

By voting "Yes," you agree to allocate 70,000 XPLA tokens from the Community Pool as liquidity on Osmosis DEX.
By voting "No," you disagree with allocating 70,000 XPLA tokens from the Community Pool as liquidity on Osmosis DEX."

detail.title: A node upgrade proposal for EVM compatibility
detail.description:
This is Alfred from Team XPLA.

This proposal seeks to enhance the XPLA Mainnet by upgrading its Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM) module.

The Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM) allows for the execution of Ethereum's Solidity language within XPLA. Upon approval, XPLA will have the capability to run Solidity based programs.

detail.title: Proposal for ‘Relief Fund Support’
detail.description:
This is Alfred from Team XPLA.

Genesis Holders who have been with XPLA since the beginning have been heavily impacted by FTX and are in a difficult situation.

In an effort to ease the sorrow and pain of individual holders adversely affected by the FTX incident, Team XPLA from XPLA Chain proposes the ‘Relief Fund Support’ program. 'Relief Fund Support' program has been designed to support individuals who were unable to withdraw their $XPLA as a result of the FTX incident.

Team XPLA aims to provide material support to the affected Genesis Holders with the tokens from the Reserve upon receiving the creditor’s rights from the relevant authorities. If the proposal passes, the $XPLAs we retrieve back from FTX when their bankruptcy proceeding ends will be transferred back to the Reserve or permanently removed from circulation by burning them.

· Purpose of the Proposal:

It is an agenda to propose a volume transfer to a Contract to raise the quantity (19,600,000 $XPLA) confirmed through a Scope Investigation survey and use it as a financial resource for the individual holders who have been affected by FTX. After that, $XPLA raised by this proposal will be used to support the holders who have been affected by the FTX incident.

For more information, please refer to the article below.

· URL: https://link.medium.com/ZRxevSSMJwb

* The payment method and its date may vary depending on the circumstances.

detail.title: Xpla reward
detail.description: (Proposer: We are DELIGHT, the genesis validator of Xpla.) This proposal aims to distribute the delegation reward of XPLA the foundation holds, as the first step in the economy implementation for providing a sufficient amount of staking rewards while maintaining the advantage of XPLA, which is no inflation. The reward that the foundation earns will be allocated as follows. 20% is transferred to the reward pool and evenly shared with all stakers over 1 year, and 79% is transferred to the community pool. The rest 1% is sent to the reserve account owned by the foundation.
